{
  "texts": [
    "Beginners often find learning to program difficult, and they have to invest a significant amount of time to write and debug their code [5,53].",
    "This process can be frustrating and lead to doubts about their ability to learn to program [20,36].",
    "Meanwhile, the notable increase in the enrollment of intro CS courses makes one-on-one guidance from human experts hard to scale in large classrooms [18,54].",
    "Recently, large language models (LLMs) have opened up new ways for timely, adaptive, and scalable programming support [46].",
    "For example, they can create complete programs directly from natural language input [30,44]."
  ]
}